ntità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003524-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text after Bitto and Orsi.</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>A Greek sententia at the entrance to a tomb with Latin epitaph</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Orsi 1916 176-178 fig. 41 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001701\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001701</a>  </li><li> Bitto 2001 17 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000029\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000029</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Regular deeply v-cut letters with some curvature on longer strokes. Lunate sigma and epsilon; kappa has short arms. Elegant hedera at end of line 1. Phi in line 1 and Iota in line 3 are extended.</p> Line 1-2  45  Line 3  40  Interlineation line 1 to 3  14-15  </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
